main event: A person reported seeing an unidentified object in the sky near Aurora, Ohio on June 26, 1967.
interesting points: The object was observed for about 2 minutes.
The observation was a ground visual sighting.
The report states there was 'insufficient data for evaluation' and that the case would be re-evaluated.
The Air Force requested the witness to complete an additional UFO report form to assist in the evaluation.
The witness mentioned having more UFO report forms, suggesting additional sightings or cases.
